The paper deals with task allocation and execution in multi-robot teams, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework involves adaptive decision-making and updating of parameters, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The framework also involves coordination and control of multiple agents, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of specialization parameters and updating them on-the-fly suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.MA). Finally, the paper involves simulations and experiments to demonstrate the efficacy of the proposed approach, which suggests the use of statistical and machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
